provisions.content:
In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context,—
(a)        “Board” means the Board of Governors established under section 5;
(b)        “Centre” means the 1[Global Climate-Change] Impact Studies Centre
(GCISC) established under section 3;
(c)         “Chairman” means the Chairman of the Board;
(d)         “employees” means persons employed by the Centre;
(e)        “Executive Director” means the Executive Director of the Centre appointed
under section 9;
(f)        “Fund” means the 1[Global Climate-Change] Impact Studies Centre Fund
established under section 10;
(g)         “prescribed” means prescribed by rules; and
1
Subs. by the Global Change Impact Studies Centre (Amdt.) Act No VI of 2023, s.2.
(h)        “research studies” means theoretical or experimental research work, including
modeling and simulation techniques undertaken to acquire knowledge of
fundamental principles of the climate change phenomenon and its impacts.
1[Global Climate-Change] IMPACT STUDIES CENTRE
